Industrial Security Specialist

Raytheon Technologies is seeking a Industrial Security Specialist in Sandy, Utah.
Job Description :

The candidate will support a remote program security office. The responsibilities include, but are not limited to:
Administering the security procedures (NISPOM, DoDM 5205.07 series, Intelligence Community Directive (ICD) 705, and JSIG), as they relate to operating in a classified environment for: personnel processing, media control, marking and control of documents / materials, security education, visitor control, destruction of classified information;
Develop, prepare, and implement local Standard Operating Procedures (SOP), Operations Security (OPSEC) Plans;
Provide security oversight and management to subcontractors and subordinate business units via the DD Form 254 or other contractual methods ;
Maintain a secure facility in accordance with (IAW) ICD 705;
Oversee specialized procedures for the transmission of classified and/or proprietary material/information;
Conduct and/or participate in internal reviews and/or Government inspections;
Investigate security infractions/violations and prepare reports specifying the potential for loss or compromise and the associated risk to the program(s);
Collaborate and assist the ISSO / ISSM on implementation of JSIG requirements;
Perform general Administrative roles acting as remote site admin;
Perform general IT support acting as local IT point of contact ;
This position requires an active TS/SCI with poly

Required Skills:
Bachelor’s Degree;
Knowledge and experience in site security and relevant security classifications and procedures related to personnel processing, media control, marking and control of documents, materials, security education, visitor control and destruction of classified information;
Proficient in Microsoft Office applications;
Ability to multi-task and prioritize;
Friendly and professional demeanor;
Customer service oriented.
Minimum 5 years of experience

Desired Skills:

Familiarity with JPAS, Access Commander and CCURE
Experience in a customer service position/similar role

Required Education (including Major):
Degree major in Business Management, Security and/or Risk Management, Government Policy, Information Management, Criminal Justice, or other related field of study.

